Digital Channel Cfg_DelayOn and Cfg_DelayOff added ============================================================ Instruction Overview: ----- Large majority of process related control strategies require digital field signals. The Digital Channel instruction (raM_Dvc_DigitalChannel) provides the minimum required functionality for abstracting these digital signals into a usable format. This allows the user to develop a control strategy without requiring knowledge of where the physical signals are sourced, making the control strategy logic I/O agnostic and therefore portable across all Logix platforms without modification. The following primary functionalities are provided: 1. Signal Transfer 2. Signal Quality Indication 3. Signal Forcing 4. Signal Delay 5. Virtualization
Instruction Execution: ----- Continuous
Supplemental Descriptions: ----- Signal Transfer – Transfer the input signal to the output.
Signal Quality – Signal quality indicator is an accumulation of all conditions that can have a negative effect on the digital signal fidelity. Components of the quality indicator include input module health, communication link status, digital Channel health and status, field wiring status, and so forth.
Signal Substitution – A substitute signal can be manually set via HMI, providing a means of separating the logical signal value from the physical digital I/O point.
Signal Delay – The physical signal’s off-to-on and on-to-off transitions can be delayed. Applicable for Channel Type selected as Input.
Virtual – A status indicator is provided to show when the I/O connection and data is to, or from, a source other than the module.
Revision Notes: ----- 1.1.00 – Cfg_DelayOn and Cfg_DelayOff added 1.0.00 – Release
